abstract: A new study showed success in implanting one embryo, rather than two or more.
snippet: A new study showed success in implanting one embryo, rather than two or more.
lead_paragraph: A few years ago, a friend, who, like many of our peers, got started late in the baby game and ended up going the  in vitro fertilization route, told me she was pregnant with twins. They'd used two embryos to maximize the chance of getting pregnant, and both had taken. But they didn't want twins. The next time I saw her, she had one baby.

headline.main: I.V.F. Without the Risk of Multiple Births?
